WEBVTT

00:01.171 --> 00:06.171
(film roll rattling)
(soft dramatic music)

00:10.062 --> 00:12.550
(soft dramatic music)

00:12.550 --> 00:13.780
- [Rianne] On the first day class,

00:13.780 --> 00:15.930
Professor Rossi walked in and said,

00:15.930 --> 00:17.520
it is completely normal for a man

00:17.520 --> 00:19.800
to come back home from work,
hit the head of his wife

00:19.800 --> 00:22.570
against the kitchen table and kill her.

00:22.570 --> 00:26.167
Remember, we're still the
most dangerous animal.

00:26.167 --> 00:29.334
(soft dramatic music)

00:33.855 --> 00:38.855
(throat clearing)
(soft dramatic music)

00:40.670 --> 00:45.490
- Honey, can you please pick
up your brother on Wednesday?

00:45.490 --> 00:46.930
- How 'bout you send a taxi to get him?

00:46.930 --> 00:48.363
- God, no.

00:50.880 --> 00:51.900
If you don't want to pick him up,

00:51.900 --> 00:53.503
then I will figure out a way.

00:54.950 --> 00:55.783
- No, Mom, it's fine.

00:55.783 --> 00:56.616
I'll pick him up.

00:56.616 --> 00:57.449
It's fine.

00:58.490 --> 01:01.620
I just want you to answer
something for me first.

01:01.620 --> 01:02.453
- What's that?

01:03.930 --> 01:06.720
- Would you visit me twice a
month if I went to prison, too?

01:06.720 --> 01:09.262
- Of course not.

01:09.262 --> 01:11.612
No matter what you did,
they'd never catch you.

01:13.500 --> 01:15.760
- That's not a valid answer.

01:15.760 --> 01:19.063
- It's not the answer that you
wanted, but it is an answer.

01:20.410 --> 01:21.470
Wednesday at 10.

01:21.470 --> 01:23.100
Please don't be late.

01:23.100 --> 01:25.090
- It's not what I asked.

01:25.090 --> 01:28.893
- And please do not get in his case.

01:29.810 --> 01:31.810
Okay, it's the last thing that he needs.

01:32.770 --> 01:34.493
- Sure, promise.

01:46.008 --> 01:47.880
(hand knocking)

01:47.880 --> 01:49.180
- Hey you.

01:49.180 --> 01:51.000
Hey, are you back with us this term?

01:51.000 --> 01:52.630
Wait, did you register with me?

01:52.630 --> 01:53.808
How was vacation?

01:53.808 --> 01:55.358
Did we talk about that already?

01:56.560 --> 01:58.039
- Yes, this is my final term.

01:58.039 --> 02:00.360
Yes, I chose you as my
advisor for my senior project

02:00.360 --> 02:01.950
so I'm already registered.

02:01.950 --> 02:03.320
No, it wasn't a vacation.

02:03.320 --> 02:05.570
It was a leave of absence to
come back with a vengeance.

02:05.570 --> 02:07.000
And no we haven't talked about it already.

02:07.000 --> 02:08.080
Am I interrupting?

02:08.080 --> 02:09.080
- Absolutely.

02:09.080 --> 02:11.450
Everybody waited last minute to register.

02:11.450 --> 02:12.283
- Guilty as charged.

02:12.283 --> 02:13.116
Sorry.

02:13.116 --> 02:14.760
Didn't know if I was gonna
be able to afford the time.

02:14.760 --> 02:16.250
- Well, at least you're
one of the good ones,

02:16.250 --> 02:17.860
so I can let it slide.

02:17.860 --> 02:19.870
Anyway, if this is a social visit,

02:19.870 --> 02:20.847
can we reschedule to next week?

02:20.847 --> 02:23.067
'Cause I am really busy.

02:23.067 --> 02:25.530
- Yeah, I actually wanted to talk

02:25.530 --> 02:27.357
to you about my senior project.

02:27.357 --> 02:30.460
- You are making it about
your brother's case, right?

02:30.460 --> 02:32.940
- But Nick is actually getting out soon.

02:32.940 --> 02:34.380
- [Rossi] Already?

02:34.380 --> 02:36.016
- [Rianne] Time flies.

02:36.016 --> 02:37.810
I'm thinking I should just move on

02:37.810 --> 02:39.160
and work on something else.

02:40.571 --> 02:43.190
- Cool your jets, space girl.

02:43.190 --> 02:45.390
How close are you to him?

02:45.390 --> 02:48.180
Because you've been working
on his case for years.

02:48.180 --> 02:50.090
If you push through, you could even write

02:50.090 --> 02:52.430
that book you always talk about.

02:52.430 --> 02:53.963
- It would be too personal.

02:55.662 --> 02:58.002
- Let me be blunt here.

02:58.002 --> 03:03.002
You have never been a normal
person and you never will be.

03:03.010 --> 03:05.200
And yes, I know when I'm
talking about weirdos,

03:05.200 --> 03:07.220
I'm the worst one out there,

03:07.220 --> 03:09.680
but you have to embrace what you're about

03:09.680 --> 03:11.790
and push beyond that.

03:11.790 --> 03:13.053
You know this already.

03:13.908 --> 03:15.440
You have a beautiful mind.

03:15.440 --> 03:16.662
Use it.

03:16.662 --> 03:19.963
Just be the hunter you are meant to be.

03:20.980 --> 03:23.160
- I was talking more about his feelings,

03:23.160 --> 03:25.469
but I guess you kind of have a point.

03:25.469 --> 03:26.569
- Kind of?

03:26.569 --> 03:28.973
You just came here for
the pep talk, didn't you?

03:30.579 --> 03:31.540
Come on, pitch it to me.

03:31.540 --> 03:32.940
Rough is fine.

03:32.940 --> 03:33.773
Just shoot.

03:35.860 --> 03:38.490
- Passion crimes is a
gateway to serial killing.

03:38.490 --> 03:39.870
- Wow, I love it.

03:39.870 --> 03:42.680
Wait, are you saying you think

03:42.680 --> 03:44.840
your brother's gonna kill more people?

03:44.840 --> 03:47.690
- I was thinking of using him
as the passion crimes part.

03:48.642 --> 03:50.043
- I'm sold.

03:50.043 --> 03:52.510
Just iron it up and send me the layout.

03:52.510 --> 03:53.660
- Oh, well now, hold on.

03:53.660 --> 03:54.829
I didn't say I was gonna do it.

03:54.829 --> 03:57.810
I wanna see how things are
with Nick at home first.

03:57.810 --> 04:01.300
- Well, come back when you've
made up your mind, okay.

04:01.300 --> 04:02.133
Bye now.

04:03.600 --> 04:04.433
- Will due.

04:04.433 --> 04:05.700
Thanks.

04:05.700 --> 04:07.250
- A pleasure as always.

04:07.250 --> 04:08.200
- [Rianne] Bye now.

04:17.829 --> 04:19.893
- I guess this is as good a spot as any.

04:21.100 --> 04:22.850
So the big question is-

04:22.850 --> 04:24.347
- Whoa, are you proposing?

04:24.347 --> 04:25.560
No, no, no, no, no.

04:25.560 --> 04:26.393
Don't, don't, don't.

04:26.393 --> 04:27.370
I don't want you to propose.

04:27.370 --> 04:28.203
No.

04:28.203 --> 04:29.550
- I'm just asking you want to eat here.

04:29.550 --> 04:32.550
- Oh, you made it sound like a big moment.

04:32.550 --> 04:33.763
Yes, I am starving.

04:40.347 --> 04:42.253
I don't wanna pick him up.

04:43.640 --> 04:45.490
- Is he really dangerous?

04:45.490 --> 04:47.363
- No, he's just an asshole.

04:52.770 --> 04:54.990
Professor Rossi is right.

04:54.990 --> 04:56.133
This could be my book.

04:57.330 --> 05:00.500
- Boo, you don't even like your brother.

05:00.500 --> 05:03.420
You probably won't see him
again after you graduate.

05:03.420 --> 05:05.368
Do what's best for you.

05:05.368 --> 05:09.705
Nobody cares about your
future as much as you do.

05:09.705 --> 05:12.318
Except me of course.

05:12.318 --> 05:14.420
I just wanna know about your future,

05:14.420 --> 05:16.973
so I can plan around your crazy fantasies.

05:18.018 --> 05:20.447
- Can you imagine how boring
your life would be without me?

05:20.447 --> 05:23.240
You're always so predictable and stable.

05:23.240 --> 05:24.073
- Oh yeah.

05:24.073 --> 05:26.246
I fantasize about it all the time.

05:26.246 --> 05:27.143
- Babe.

05:28.490 --> 05:31.923
- But I wouldn't trade
my boo for anything ever.

05:34.747 --> 05:36.570
- What would I do without you?

05:36.570 --> 05:39.778
- You'd probably just slowly drift away.

05:39.778 --> 05:41.244
- Mm hm.

05:41.244 --> 05:44.411
(soft dramatic music)

06:20.260 --> 06:21.593
Sorry, I'm late.

06:23.866 --> 06:26.676
- What's up with the costume?

06:26.676 --> 06:28.143
- It's not a costume.

06:30.058 --> 06:32.073
- Whatever you say, Marilyn Manson.

06:34.500 --> 06:36.290
- Look, I wanna be left alone.

06:36.290 --> 06:37.230
You wanna be left alone.

06:37.230 --> 06:39.010
Let's just stay out of
each other's way, okay.

06:39.010 --> 06:39.843
- Or else?

06:41.751 --> 06:44.673
- What do you want from me, Nick?

06:44.673 --> 06:47.840
(soft dramatic music)

06:49.180 --> 06:51.570
- I want you help me find Gwen's killer.

06:51.570 --> 06:52.923
- Seriously?

06:52.923 --> 06:53.915
You haven't even been out a day

06:53.915 --> 06:55.350
and that's what's on your mind?

06:55.350 --> 06:56.640
- What else you want me to think about?

06:56.640 --> 06:58.962
Going to a costume party with you?

06:58.962 --> 07:01.180
- Can't you just move on?

07:01.180 --> 07:03.289
- No, I can't just move on.

07:03.289 --> 07:04.560
If you've ever been in
love, then you'd know that.

07:04.560 --> 07:06.260
- Oh, you think you're the first person

07:06.260 --> 07:07.970
to fall in love like ever?

07:07.970 --> 07:09.700
- No, but compared to
you I'm a fucking expert.

07:09.700 --> 07:11.867
- Oh yeah, you were in one
relationship in you're an expert.

07:11.867 --> 07:12.949
- It wasn't one relationship.

07:12.949 --> 07:14.300
It was the relationship.

07:14.300 --> 07:15.920
- [Rianne] Okay, Nick.

07:15.920 --> 07:17.064
- [Nick] So you're gonna help me or not?

07:17.064 --> 07:18.300
- No.

07:18.300 --> 07:19.400
Of course not.

07:19.400 --> 07:20.920
Okay, can't you tell that the entire rest

07:20.920 --> 07:22.263
of the world has moved on?

07:24.330 --> 07:29.003
- You know, Gwen always
tried to include you in it.

07:33.507 --> 07:35.403
- Are you guilt tripping me?

07:37.762 --> 07:38.933
- How can I?

07:38.933 --> 07:40.384
You don't care about anybody.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.280
- Please.

07:43.280 --> 07:44.113
- All right.

07:45.790 --> 07:48.690
Guess just have to do it myself.

07:48.690 --> 07:49.523
- Oh yeah.

07:49.523 --> 07:51.843
And what are you gonna do
when you find him, kill him?

07:56.170 --> 07:59.233
You know, you can't go around
saying things like that.

07:59.233 --> 08:00.683
At least not in front of mom.

08:02.270 --> 08:04.930
- You could pretend to
tolerate me, Rianne,

08:04.930 --> 08:06.873
at least in front of mom.

08:06.873 --> 08:07.763
- I told you.

08:08.850 --> 08:10.370
You leave me alone, I'll leave you alone.

08:10.370 --> 08:11.430
- Fine, let's do that.

08:11.430 --> 08:12.563
- Okay, let's do that.

08:22.880 --> 08:24.960
- He really thought you
weren't gonna leave him a tip.

08:24.960 --> 08:25.793
- I thought about it.

08:25.793 --> 08:28.430
You expect me to behave
like a lady when I'm hungry.

08:28.430 --> 08:30.200
- His face was priceless.

08:30.200 --> 08:32.053
I don't think I can let you do that.

08:33.269 --> 08:35.970
- Maybe he's just from France, babe.

08:35.970 --> 08:38.159
- No way in hell he's French, boo.

08:38.159 --> 08:41.063
His accent changed like
15 times during the meal.

08:46.362 --> 08:47.453
- What is it?

08:49.040 --> 08:50.300
- My mom.

08:50.300 --> 08:53.090
She just drained all the
money from my account.

08:53.090 --> 08:54.797
- I'm sorry, babe.

08:54.797 --> 08:56.630
- It was a matter of time.

08:56.630 --> 08:58.300
She can't say no to him.

08:58.300 --> 09:00.200
- Yeah, but it didn't even take a day.

09:03.941 --> 09:07.868
We're not gonna let this
bring us down, all right?

09:07.868 --> 09:10.563
We'll get through this
just like we always do.

09:11.540 --> 09:15.110
Plus you have me, the hottest, smartest,

09:15.110 --> 09:16.500
bestest girlfriend ever.

09:16.500 --> 09:17.390
- Bestest?

09:17.390 --> 09:18.430
Really, babe?

09:18.430 --> 09:19.540
- You're such a grammar Nazi.

09:19.540 --> 09:21.850
- I'm just saying bestest is not a word.

09:21.850 --> 09:23.330
- Stop, stop.

09:23.330 --> 09:26.127
This is about me supporting you.

09:26.127 --> 09:27.927
Don't you try to change the subject.

09:30.750 --> 09:33.773
Just remember I love you tons.

09:34.820 --> 09:35.653
- [Rianne] Okay.

09:35.653 --> 09:37.310
- Anyway, this cute brain of yours

09:37.310 --> 09:39.760
probably came up with a
plan for this months ago.

09:42.663 --> 09:45.830
(soft dramatic music)

09:54.680 --> 09:56.540
- I understand how you feel,
bro, but what are you gonna do?

09:56.540 --> 09:58.890
Go around and ask if they
killed your girlfriend?

09:58.890 --> 09:59.820
- No.

09:59.820 --> 10:01.630
I'm gonna ask if they know who killed her.

10:01.630 --> 10:03.690
Pay good money for it, too.

10:03.690 --> 10:05.570
- It's only gonna mess with
your head trying to figure out

10:05.570 --> 10:07.950
if the leads they give you are true.

10:07.950 --> 10:08.810
- Well if you have a better idea-

10:08.810 --> 10:10.040
- I do.

10:10.040 --> 10:13.703
Get a job, move on, try to
catch up with your life.

10:15.199 --> 10:18.477
- You know I can't do that, man.

10:18.477 --> 10:20.413
- Well, if you change your mind,

10:21.299 --> 10:23.477
my boss agreed to meet with you.

10:23.477 --> 10:25.500
It's not an interview though.

10:25.500 --> 10:28.453
It's more of a meet and
greet type of thing.

10:28.453 --> 10:29.370
- Thanks, man.

10:29.370 --> 10:30.203
That's cool.

10:30.203 --> 10:31.036
Thanks, man.

10:34.370 --> 10:35.977
Is this the company?

10:35.977 --> 10:38.863
- No, that's a taxi service
I do through the phone.

10:40.890 --> 10:41.820
- Sounds legit.

10:41.820 --> 10:42.653
Does it pay well?

10:42.653 --> 10:43.830
Maybe I can do that.

10:43.830 --> 10:45.344
- Pays all right.

10:45.344 --> 10:47.223
You just wouldn't qualify.

10:48.890 --> 10:49.723
Sorry.

10:50.660 --> 10:51.493
- True.

10:54.630 --> 10:55.710
- [Julian] You wanna see something cool?

10:55.710 --> 10:57.079
- [Nick] Sure.

10:57.079 --> 10:58.483
- [Julian] Check this out.

10:59.620 --> 11:00.453
- [Nick] What's that?

11:00.453 --> 11:01.286
- A camera.

11:04.274 --> 11:06.016
- What do you mean a camera?

11:06.016 --> 11:07.099
No, it's not.

11:09.293 --> 11:10.330
- It's HD, bro.

11:10.330 --> 11:11.981
Sometimes people get rowdy.

11:11.981 --> 11:12.814
- [Nick] What the fuck?

11:12.814 --> 11:13.913
This thing is puny.

11:15.160 --> 11:17.223
- And it's motion activated, right.

11:18.580 --> 11:20.450
Cool or not cool?

11:20.450 --> 11:22.305
- Really fucking cool.

11:22.305 --> 11:23.138
Holy.

11:28.970 --> 11:30.580
Man.

11:30.580 --> 11:31.413
Things change.

11:34.610 --> 11:36.490
- Listen, I know Gwen
was something else but-

11:36.490 --> 11:37.323
- Stop.

11:37.323 --> 11:38.156
- [Julian] You should be open to the idea.

11:38.156 --> 11:38.989
- Stop.

11:38.989 --> 11:40.009
- [Julian] I'm seeing a
super cute girl right now.

11:40.009 --> 11:40.842
- Quit it.

11:40.842 --> 11:42.740
- [Julian] It's not too
serious, but it's really nice

11:42.740 --> 11:44.140
to have someone else around.

11:49.227 --> 11:50.190
- It's gonna take me a second

11:50.190 --> 11:52.033
to start thinking about girls again, man.

11:54.730 --> 11:57.283
- Anyway, I gotta get back to work, man.

11:57.283 --> 11:58.116
- Yeah.

11:59.640 --> 12:01.428
- Just one more thing though.

12:01.428 --> 12:02.261
- What?

12:03.900 --> 12:06.920
- I didn't tell my boss
why you went to prison,

12:06.920 --> 12:09.687
so when you meet with her
just don't go into details.

12:09.687 --> 12:11.339
You know what I mean?

12:11.339 --> 12:14.089
- Yeah, I wasn't planning to but.

12:15.990 --> 12:17.060
Thanks a lot for the hookup, man.

12:17.060 --> 12:18.753
- Yeah, yeah, got you.

12:19.677 --> 12:21.377
You might wanna take care of this.

12:23.090 --> 12:23.923
- Care of what?

12:24.920 --> 12:25.783
- All that.

12:33.130 --> 12:35.000
- Shit, I didn't even think about it.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.420
- Yeah bro, you gotta
look good to feel good.

12:37.420 --> 12:39.420
Right now you don't look good at all so.

12:41.780 --> 12:42.613
- Yeah.

12:44.600 --> 12:46.174
Yeah.

12:46.174 --> 12:47.007
Well thanks, man.

12:47.007 --> 12:47.840
- [Julian] Yeah.

12:57.600 --> 12:59.223
- I like this new look, hon.

13:00.110 --> 13:02.147
It suits you.

13:02.147 --> 13:03.840
- It's not like I wasn't gonna clean up

13:03.840 --> 13:05.320
before going to my interviews.

13:05.320 --> 13:06.153
- Wait.

13:06.153 --> 13:07.490
You got an interview already?

13:07.490 --> 13:08.630
- It's like those manifestation books

13:08.630 --> 13:10.130
you gave me always say, right.

13:12.950 --> 13:14.900
- Everything finds its place.

13:14.900 --> 13:16.720
- [Nick] It's finally happening, Mom.

13:16.720 --> 13:17.700
Yeah, yeah.

13:17.700 --> 13:20.073
Better enjoy me while I
still got free time, kid.

13:21.860 --> 13:23.364
- What do you mean?

13:23.364 --> 13:27.055
- Well, I told you that your
brother is staying with us.

13:27.055 --> 13:28.222
- Permanently?

13:29.254 --> 13:30.600
- Why are you defensive?

13:30.600 --> 13:32.800
Didn't I drive you to your
piano lessons every week

13:32.800 --> 13:34.420
when you had to become a virtuoso.

13:34.420 --> 13:37.130
- Yeah, so you could take
the car and screw Gwen.

13:37.130 --> 13:38.570
- Yeah well, what about when I bought

13:38.570 --> 13:39.613
your classmates lunch every Saturday

13:39.613 --> 13:40.980
because you were too much of a nerd

13:40.980 --> 13:41.813
to make your own friends?

13:41.813 --> 13:42.690
- Yeah, every penny Mom gave you,

13:42.690 --> 13:44.740
then you would use it to impress Gwen.

13:44.740 --> 13:45.573
- Well, it worked out, didn't it?

13:45.573 --> 13:46.750
Because she was crazy about me.

13:46.750 --> 13:48.540
- Mm hm, how'd it work out for her?

13:48.540 --> 13:49.440
- Stop it, Rianne.

13:55.970 --> 14:00.970
Anyway, I am very happy
that you're starting

14:01.110 --> 14:02.960
to think about your future already.

14:02.960 --> 14:03.793
- Yeah.

14:05.868 --> 14:07.470
Talking about the future.

14:07.470 --> 14:08.303
I was.

14:10.760 --> 14:11.800
- What is going on?

14:11.800 --> 14:14.680
- I was talking to your
brother about the fact

14:14.680 --> 14:16.690
that you and Mariah spend
so much time together

14:16.690 --> 14:19.333
and you might be moving in with her soon.

14:21.360 --> 14:23.520
- Are you kicking me out?

14:23.520 --> 14:24.580
- No.

14:24.580 --> 14:27.521
We're just planning ahead, that's all.

14:27.521 --> 14:28.460
- What's next?

14:28.460 --> 14:30.488
Selling my organs to pay for his new suit?

14:30.488 --> 14:35.423
- Well Mom did always say that
you eat really healthy so.

14:35.423 --> 14:38.590
(soft dramatic music)

15:09.093 --> 15:10.233
It's okay, kid.

15:11.206 --> 15:14.700
Thought I'd apologize for spazzing out.

15:14.700 --> 15:17.340
- Why are you always such an asshole?

15:17.340 --> 15:19.990
- Oh probably because you're
always such a snowflake.

15:22.420 --> 15:23.253
You moving out?

15:25.534 --> 15:30.293
- Look, I can't help
you with your project,

15:33.600 --> 15:35.603
but this might be a good place to start.

15:37.060 --> 15:37.893
- What's that?

15:40.370 --> 15:41.890
- After the cops left your place,

15:41.890 --> 15:43.300
I took anything that I thought might be

15:43.300 --> 15:44.463
of sentimental value.

15:48.400 --> 15:49.233
- My stuff?

15:50.510 --> 15:51.803
- Mostly Gwen's.

15:52.960 --> 15:53.948
I think.

15:53.948 --> 15:57.115
(soft dramatic music)

