Only cleaning up.

56:40.210 --> 56:41.310
- That explains a lot.

56:50.388 --> 56:51.721
I almost forgot.

56:55.610 --> 56:57.490
Julian Hansen.

56:57.490 --> 56:59.680
Apparently he was one of Gwen's lovers.

56:59.680 --> 57:00.930
I missed him the first time around.

57:00.930 --> 57:02.660
Didn't get to talk to him.

57:02.660 --> 57:04.100
- How did you miss him?

57:04.100 --> 57:05.680
- He's Nick's best friend.

57:05.680 --> 57:07.870
He was right in front of me so.

57:07.870 --> 57:09.570
But hopefully I'll talk to him soon.

57:09.570 --> 57:10.503
Maybe this week.

57:11.870 --> 57:12.893
- Another suspect.

57:14.210 --> 57:16.990
- Just another one of her men.

57:16.990 --> 57:17.823
- Well.

57:18.750 --> 57:19.910
Go get him.

57:19.910 --> 57:22.910
(suspenseful music)

57:34.760 --> 57:35.593
- Hey, honey.

57:39.760 --> 57:40.593
Are you okay?

57:45.880 --> 57:47.280
- When did I fuck it all up?

57:52.770 --> 57:53.770
I had it all, right?

57:54.680 --> 57:56.940
And then poof, I'm in prison.

57:56.940 --> 57:58.190
Nobody comes to visit me.

58:00.500 --> 58:02.333
- It was a complicated case.

58:05.038 --> 58:06.423
- Complicated how?

58:11.146 --> 58:11.979
- Well.

58:14.700 --> 58:17.370
For instance, it came up during the trial

58:19.110 --> 58:22.923
that Gwen was how should I say?

58:25.400 --> 58:26.903
Crazy about boys.

58:29.150 --> 58:31.503
And some of them were
your so called friends.

58:34.970 --> 58:36.520
- You never thought to tell me.

58:38.050 --> 58:38.883
- Why?

58:39.973 --> 58:42.640
She wasn't serious about any of them

58:43.600 --> 58:46.490
and it certainly wouldn't
have helped your case.

58:46.490 --> 58:49.780
It only would've made you feel
worse than you already were.

58:50.710 --> 58:52.810
- You could've saved me so much time, Mom.

58:56.400 --> 58:58.210
Now I'm trying to pick
up the pieces of my life

58:58.210 --> 59:00.160
and the only person I have left is you.

59:05.350 --> 59:07.917
- You were very checked
out during the trial.

59:09.700 --> 59:11.083
I did my best.

59:14.760 --> 59:15.593
Anyway.

59:16.550 --> 59:18.623
Julian got you that job interview today.

59:22.490 --> 59:23.590
- Wasn't an interview.

59:24.890 --> 59:27.543
Lady just wanted to see the
ex-con fresh out of jail.

59:28.540 --> 59:30.270
Made me so fucking angry.

59:32.000 --> 59:33.103
- Did Julian know?

59:33.103 --> 59:34.353
- I don't know.

59:35.300 --> 59:36.890
He wasn't there.

59:36.890 --> 59:38.690
He's not answering his phone either.

59:43.600 --> 59:47.390
- Maybe you could just
get away for a little bit.

59:47.390 --> 59:48.223
Take a vacation.

59:51.130 --> 59:55.050
I have some money saved up for
Rianne's graduation present.

59:55.050 --> 59:56.800
I could easily just-

59:56.800 --> 1:00:00.020
- All the money in the world
couldn't help me now, Mom.

1:00:01.760 --> 1:00:02.593
Thanks though.

1:00:03.903 --> 1:00:07.070
(soft dramatic music)

1:00:14.870 --> 1:00:16.920
- Long time no see, stranger.

1:00:16.920 --> 1:00:19.251
- Thanks for buying groceries yesterday.

1:00:19.251 --> 1:00:20.084
- Yeah, no problem.

1:00:20.084 --> 1:00:21.560
I figured you were back to double shifting

1:00:21.560 --> 1:00:24.785
trying to make up for your big withdrawal.

1:00:24.785 --> 1:00:26.035
- Please don't.

1:00:33.140 --> 1:00:36.630
Have you spoke to Mariah
about moving in together yet?

1:00:36.630 --> 1:00:39.670
- Mom, I told you we'd talk
about when I finish school.

1:00:39.670 --> 1:00:41.220
Nick can wait that much longer.

1:00:43.560 --> 1:00:44.730
- But you have to remember

1:00:44.730 --> 1:00:47.510
that he needs more help than other people.

1:00:47.510 --> 1:00:49.030
He always has.

1:00:49.030 --> 1:00:50.680
He used to have this gate

1:00:50.680 --> 1:00:52.850
that all the other kids laughed at.

1:00:52.850 --> 1:00:54.120
- And he laughed along with them

1:00:54.120 --> 1:00:56.330
because he was too little to understand

1:00:56.330 --> 1:00:58.323
that they were laughing at him.

1:01:02.360 --> 1:01:03.500
I know.

1:01:03.500 --> 1:01:05.193
You told me many times.

1:01:06.230 --> 1:01:08.280
- And then you started growing up

1:01:08.280 --> 1:01:10.940
and doing everything on your own.

1:01:10.940 --> 1:01:12.410
- Yup, so you had to bring me down

1:01:12.410 --> 1:01:14.510
to make him feel less inadequate.

1:01:14.510 --> 1:01:18.070
- He is your brother and he needs us.

1:01:18.070 --> 1:01:20.723
Is that too much to ask?

1:01:21.787 --> 1:01:24.553
- Mom, Mariah's waiting for me.

1:01:24.553 --> 1:01:25.743
- Goddammit, Rianne.

1:01:27.938 --> 1:01:30.690
What is it gonna take for
you to care for your brother?

1:01:30.690 --> 1:01:31.790
- Why?

1:01:31.790 --> 1:01:33.658
He's just gonna throw
everything away anyway.

1:01:33.658 --> 1:01:34.491
- We'll help him.

1:01:34.491 --> 1:01:37.252
- People like him can't be helped, Mom.

1:01:37.252 --> 1:01:40.419
(soft dramatic music)

1:02:03.923 --> 1:02:04.756
I'm sorry.

1:02:06.075 --> 1:02:09.242
(soft dramatic music)

1:02:26.030 --> 1:02:28.770
Babe, today's one of those days
where I need our safe space.

1:02:28.770 --> 1:02:30.083
- Who's Katie Morrison?

1:02:31.600 --> 1:02:32.860
- What?

1:02:32.860 --> 1:02:35.740
- You left your email
account open in my computer,

1:02:35.740 --> 1:02:38.130
but it wasn't even your account.

1:02:38.130 --> 1:02:41.310
It was Katie Morrison's
or whoever that is.

1:02:41.310 --> 1:02:43.010
- But you respected the
fact that it wasn't yours

1:02:43.010 --> 1:02:44.830
and you didn't touch anything, right babe?

1:02:44.830 --> 1:02:47.220
- Can you tell me what's going on?

1:02:47.220 --> 1:02:48.480
- Did you touch anything?

1:02:48.480 --> 1:02:49.530
- You don't trust me?

1:02:50.608 --> 1:02:53.608
(suspenseful music)

1:03:04.232 --> 1:03:05.860
- That's just research, Mariah.

1:03:05.860 --> 1:03:06.890
You'd die of boredom.

1:03:06.890 --> 1:03:09.123
- Why don't you let me decide for myself?

1:03:10.240 --> 1:03:12.020
- What are you talking about?

1:03:12.020 --> 1:03:13.943
- Nothing about you is simple, boo,

1:03:15.134 --> 1:03:17.084
but I'm really happy with us right now.

1:03:17.960 --> 1:03:20.750
If this is something that's
gonna change us, please stop.

1:03:20.750 --> 1:03:23.870
- Not everything is about us.

1:03:23.870 --> 1:03:26.560
- Anything that happens
to you happens to us.

1:03:26.560 --> 1:03:28.350
Whatever you do, we do.

1:03:28.350 --> 1:03:31.180
- We don't become one
person because we're dating.

1:03:31.180 --> 1:03:32.490
What I do is what I do.

1:03:33.542 --> 1:03:36.709
(soft dramatic music)

1:03:55.150 --> 1:03:57.653
- Love is not just about
what one person feels.

1:03:59.040 --> 1:04:02.181
It's about two people
sharing everything together.

1:04:02.181 --> 1:04:05.348
(soft dramatic music)

1:04:09.660 --> 1:04:12.960
Love is about trust and commitment.

1:04:15.068 --> 1:04:15.901
- I know.

1:04:16.930 --> 1:04:18.894
You taught me that.

1:04:18.894 --> 1:04:22.061
(soft dramatic music)

1:04:47.650 --> 1:04:49.833
I won't let anything change us.

1:05:03.310 --> 1:05:04.890
- Hi.

1:05:04.890 --> 1:05:07.010
I don't know if you remember my name.

1:05:07.010 --> 1:05:08.820
- I know who you are.

1:05:08.820 --> 1:05:10.180
I'm trying to understand
why you didn't text

1:05:10.180 --> 1:05:12.423
before showing up like normal people,

1:05:13.270 --> 1:05:16.063
but you probably got
institutionalized already, right?

1:05:17.090 --> 1:05:17.923
Nevermind.

1:05:17.923 --> 1:05:19.140
What do you want, Nick?

1:05:19.140 --> 1:05:19.973
- May I come in?

1:05:19.973 --> 1:05:20.940
- No.

1:05:20.940 --> 1:05:22.090
Just say what you need.

1:05:23.887 --> 1:05:25.087
- I'm looking for Katie.

1:05:27.218 --> 1:05:28.423
- She's dead.

1:05:30.010 --> 1:05:31.150
- Excuse me.

1:05:31.150 --> 1:05:32.470
- She's dead.

1:05:32.470 --> 1:05:34.940
She went missing in
October eight years ago

1:05:34.940 --> 1:05:36.130
a bit after Gwen was killed.

1:05:36.130 --> 1:05:37.290
You should really do your homework

1:05:37.290 --> 1:05:38.370
before going to people's homes.

1:05:38.370 --> 1:05:40.391
It's kind of wrong to just show up.

1:05:40.391 --> 1:05:42.920
- If she's missing, then
maybe she's still in hiding.

1:05:42.920 --> 1:05:44.110
- Hiding?

1:05:44.110 --> 1:05:45.191
From whom?

1:05:45.191 --> 1:05:47.350
Nobody could've kept her
in a basement too long.

1:05:47.350 --> 1:05:48.950
Katie was like a feral cat.

1:05:48.950 --> 1:05:51.510
She would've dug through
anything and anyone to break free

1:05:51.510 --> 1:05:53.380
and then come home to tell me about it.

1:05:53.380 --> 1:05:56.120
- Wouldn't you have heard her come back?

1:05:56.120 --> 1:05:57.680
- The only reason I'm talking to you

1:05:57.680 --> 1:05:59.650
is because I know you didn't kill Gwen.

1:05:59.650 --> 1:06:00.483
Whoever killed Gwen is out and about

1:06:00.483 --> 1:06:02.940
and it's the same bastard
that killed my daughter.

1:06:04.728 --> 1:06:06.336
- Got any theories?

1:06:06.336 --> 1:06:07.410
- The killer was in love with Gwen

1:06:07.410 --> 1:06:08.990
and killed her when he found
out she was with Katie.

1:06:08.990 --> 1:06:11.323
Then killed Katie out of jealously.

1:06:12.333 --> 1:06:16.700
Honestly, I think you were
probably more of a cover for Gwen

1:06:16.700 --> 1:06:18.200
to look respectable, you know.

1:06:20.039 --> 1:06:21.760
- You know, everybody keeps telling me

1:06:21.760 --> 1:06:23.713
the killer was involved with Gwen, too.

1:06:24.632 --> 1:06:25.465
- Of course.

1:06:25.465 --> 1:06:27.610
Wasn't she stabbed 27 times?

1:06:27.610 --> 1:06:30.680
That's someone that was
hurting very, very badly.

1:06:30.680 --> 1:06:32.330
If you hadn't been in prison
when Katie went missing,

1:06:32.330 --> 1:06:33.930
I would've thought of you first.

1:06:35.032 --> 1:06:36.440
- Got anybody else in mind?

1:06:38.012 --> 1:06:40.273
- I wasn't that involved in their lives.

1:06:41.440 --> 1:06:43.090
All this thinking happened later.

1:06:44.550 --> 1:06:46.227
- You keep saying he.

1:06:46.227 --> 1:06:47.870
What if it's a she?

1:06:47.870 --> 1:06:48.840
- He, she, it.

1:06:48.840 --> 1:06:50.350
It doesn't matter.

1:06:50.350 --> 1:06:53.210
Someone with two hands and a broken heart.

1:06:53.210 --> 1:06:55.060
Anyway, I have things to do.

1:06:55.060 --> 1:06:56.068
Sorry.

1:06:56.068 --> 1:06:56.985
- Go 'head.

1:06:58.155 --> 1:07:00.530
- I meant I'm sorry you went to prison.

1:07:00.530 --> 1:07:03.010
I always thought you were a good guy.

1:07:03.010 --> 1:07:04.931
A bit dim but good.

1:07:04.931 --> 1:07:08.098
(soft dramatic music)

1:07:34.920 --> 1:07:35.753
- Katie's dead.

1:07:38.003 --> 1:07:39.953
- I thought you said she was in hiding.

1:07:44.690 --> 1:07:47.410
- I emailed her and someone replied,

1:07:47.410 --> 1:07:49.873
but I don't think it was her actually.

1:07:49.873 --> 1:07:51.593
I actually think it's Julian.

1:07:54.960 --> 1:07:56.130
- Wait, what?

1:07:56.130 --> 1:07:56.963
- Here's my theory.

1:07:56.963 --> 1:07:58.520
So.

1:07:58.520 --> 1:08:00.427
Porter, he kills all the other ones

1:08:00.427 --> 1:08:01.400
out of jealously or spite.

1:08:01.400 --> 1:08:02.320
We know that.

1:08:02.320 --> 1:08:04.820
- Can't prove it but agreed.

1:08:04.820 --> 1:08:05.653
- Okay.

1:08:05.653 --> 1:08:10.653
So what if Julian killed
Gwen and then he kills Katie?

1:08:10.842 --> 1:08:12.740
- Why would he do that?

1:08:12.740 --> 1:08:14.030
Okay, he knew all along that Gwen

1:08:14.030 --> 1:08:15.646
was getting with other people.

1:08:15.646 --> 1:08:16.478
I mean, you were her boyfriend

1:08:16.478 --> 1:08:18.521
and he didn't try and kill you.

1:08:18.521 --> 1:08:19.990
- I thought about it a lot

1:08:19.990 --> 1:08:22.920
and I think it was
because Katie is a girl.

1:08:22.920 --> 1:08:25.550
- He felt threatened by one
girl than a bunch of guys?

1:08:25.550 --> 1:08:27.112
- It's just one girl, right?

1:08:27.112 --> 1:08:28.010
I mean, she's like thee girl.

1:08:28.010 --> 1:08:31.250
Like the only girl that
Gwen was ever with.

1:08:31.250 --> 1:08:32.500
That's gotta make her special.

1:08:32.500 --> 1:08:37.500
- I don't think it makes her
special, but I see your point.

1:08:39.830 --> 1:08:44.280
So, Julian hacked Katie's
email to get you offtrack?

1:08:44.280 --> 1:08:45.680
- To push me towards Porter.

1:08:48.309 --> 1:08:50.017
- What are you gonna do?

1:08:54.050 --> 1:08:55.300
- I don't know.

1:08:56.589 --> 1:08:59.451
You know, Julian hasn't
responded to me in like two days.

1:08:59.451 --> 1:09:01.951
I actually think that he's
onto us being onto him.

1:09:03.486 --> 1:09:06.130
- Maybe we should leave it here.

1:09:06.130 --> 1:09:08.100
I mean, I have school picking up

1:09:08.100 --> 1:09:09.733
and you gotta get a job so.

1:09:10.590 --> 1:09:11.590
- Detective quitter.

1:09:12.919 --> 1:09:15.559
Throwing in the towel already, huh?

1:09:15.559 --> 1:09:17.550
- Take a step back, Nick.

1:09:17.550 --> 1:09:20.880
You're twisting your logic
to see anything as evidence.

1:09:20.880 --> 1:09:22.840
Why do you wanna stay trapped in the past?

1:09:22.840 --> 1:09:23.673
- It's not about me, kid.

1:09:23.673 --> 1:09:24.505
- Maybe it should be.

1:09:26.984 --> 1:09:30.023
You already gave up
nine years of your life.

1:09:31.057 --> 1:09:33.700
How many more are you willing to put in?

1:09:33.700 --> 1:09:36.040
- You don't have to help
me if you don't want to.

1:09:36.040 --> 1:09:38.663
- Thank you for mansplaining the obvious.

1:09:38.663 --> 1:09:41.830
(soft dramatic music)

1:09:47.853 --> 1:09:48.687
- Rianne.

1:09:52.030 --> 1:09:54.112
I was in prison for nine years.

1:09:57.490 --> 1:10:00.440
I only got three small scars though.

1:10:00.440 --> 1:10:01.400
Do you know how crazy that is?

1:10:01.400 --> 1:10:03.343
Do you have any idea how rare?

1:10:05.690 --> 1:10:08.253
I was on like all the fucking time.

1:10:09.911 --> 1:10:11.893
I wanted to die a lot like everyday.

1:10:14.930 --> 1:10:16.690
Think about this.

1:10:16.690 --> 1:10:19.389
Thinking about this is what kept me going.

1:10:19.389 --> 1:10:21.490
This is the biggest part of a new me, man.

1:10:22.420 --> 1:10:23.952
You gotta take it or leave it.

1:10:26.050 --> 1:10:27.870
You know, it's not that
I don't wanna stop, man.

1:10:27.870 --> 1:10:29.520
It's not that I don't wanna stop.

1:10:30.963 --> 1:10:31.860
I would love to stop.

1:10:31.860 --> 1:10:32.960
I can't.

1:10:32.960 --> 1:10:33.793
I can't.

1:10:35.180 --> 1:10:36.263
- What if it is true?

1:10:37.632 --> 1:10:39.520
What are you gonna do to Julian?

1:10:39.520 --> 1:10:40.853
Don't answer that.

1:10:42.570 --> 1:10:43.520
- I gotta find him.

1:10:46.020 --> 1:10:49.282
- I can't help you be this new person.

1:10:51.490 --> 1:10:52.883
It's not good for you.

1:10:57.330 --> 1:10:58.610
- That's fine.

1:10:58.610 --> 1:10:59.893
That's fine then.

1:11:01.240 --> 1:11:03.433
You can go back to playing
with your fucking dolls.

1:11:03.433 --> 1:11:04.943
I don't give a shit, man.

1:11:07.240 --> 1:11:10.094
- Fine, I'll do that.

1:11:10.094 --> 1:11:11.907
- You do that then.

1:11:11.907 --> 1:11:14.907
(suspenseful music)

1:11:28.450 --> 1:11:29.990
- Wakey, wakey.

1:11:29.990 --> 1:11:31.297
- Five more minutes.

1:11:32.133 --> 1:11:34.460
- You can spend all day
here for all I care,

1:11:34.460 --> 1:11:35.883
but don't be late for class.

1:11:37.132 --> 1:11:39.090
- I don't care if I'm late for class.

1:11:39.090 --> 1:11:40.021
- Okay.

1:11:40.021 --> 1:11:40.973
Gotta go.

1:11:40.973 --> 1:11:41.806
Have a good one.

1:11:41.806 --> 1:11:43.050
- All right, babe.

1:11:43.050 --> 1:11:43.883
See you tonight.

1:11:45.130 --> 1:11:47.952
- Boo, if you're spending
all your time here,

1:11:47.952 --> 1:11:50.032
why don't we make it official?

1:11:51.190 --> 1:11:53.543
I'm not talking about the proposal.

1:11:54.510 --> 1:11:56.520
Just move in officially.

1:11:56.520 --> 1:11:58.230
That way you'll be closer to school,

1:11:58.230 --> 1:11:59.940
we get to spend all day together,

1:11:59.940 --> 1:12:01.889
and you won't see your brother anymore.

1:12:03.530 --> 1:12:06.620
- If I move out, there's no going back.

1:12:06.620 --> 1:12:08.420
- So you don't think it'll work out?

1:12:09.820 --> 1:12:11.362
- That's not what I said.

1:12:12.900 --> 1:12:14.200
- I know.

1:12:14.200 --> 1:12:15.866
Just think about it.

1:12:15.866 --> 1:12:16.699
Gotta go.

1:12:22.189 --> 1:12:24.100
I love you tons.

1:12:24.100 --> 1:12:25.441
- Okay.

1:12:25.441 --> 1:12:28.608
(soft dramatic music)

1:12:46.305 --> 1:12:49.360
A love obsession surviving
the object of affection.

1:12:49.360 --> 1:12:50.193
- I got your email.

1:12:50.193 --> 1:12:51.026
Sit down.

1:12:53.360 --> 1:12:55.280
Was it something I said
the last time we spoke?

1:12:55.280 --> 1:12:56.370
- Yes.

1:12:56.370 --> 1:12:58.343
Everything clicked the
last time we talked.

1:12:58.343 --> 1:13:00.490
Okay, I thought that a passion crime

1:13:00.490 --> 1:13:02.469
could reveal a part of a
person that was unknown to them

1:13:02.469 --> 1:13:04.490
and once that potential was unlocked,

1:13:04.490 --> 1:13:06.163
it could not be put away.

1:13:06.163 --> 1:13:07.920
- But now you think that obsession

1:13:07.920 --> 1:13:09.480
is helping to keep the door open.

1:13:09.480 --> 1:13:10.313
- Right.

1:13:10.313 --> 1:13:14.130
And when the obsession is
gone, the door can be closed.

1:13:14.130 --> 1:13:16.610
- But now the person
is aware of that power.

1:13:16.610 --> 1:13:18.469
The power that allowed them to correct

1:13:18.469 --> 1:13:19.580
all the wrongs done to them.

1:13:19.580 --> 1:13:21.530
Why would they give it up?

1:13:21.530 --> 1:13:25.059
- To not hurt the people around them.

1:13:25.059 --> 1:13:26.180
The other people they love.

1:13:26.180 --> 1:13:28.620
- Yet a crime has been committed.

1:13:28.620 --> 1:13:30.290
Gears have been put in motion.

1:13:30.290 --> 1:13:32.520
And consequences will come.

1:13:32.520 --> 1:13:34.580
- Okay, a passion crime is just that.

1:13:34.580 --> 1:13:36.830
A blinding moment of pain and anger,

1:13:36.830 --> 1:13:38.090
but after that the obsession

1:13:38.090 --> 1:13:40.433
just feeds itself with more vengeance.

1:13:41.280 --> 1:13:43.950
- What if the obsession is
helping to restore balance?

1:13:43.950 --> 1:13:45.280
- To the same things that twist it

1:13:45.280 --> 1:13:46.559
and corrupt it originally?

1:13:46.559 --> 1:13:48.469
- Love is the obsession.

1:13:48.469 --> 1:13:50.020
Otherwise it's just friendship.

1:13:50.020 --> 1:13:51.120
Fraternal connection.

1:13:51.120 --> 1:13:54.853
- Love is trust and commitment.

1:13:56.670 --> 1:13:58.830
- Let's say you're correct.

1:13:58.830 --> 1:14:00.480
What are you suggesting?

1:14:00.480 --> 1:14:02.610
How can you prevent the consequences?

1:14:02.610 --> 1:14:05.723
- Maybe it's not about
preventing the consequences,

1:14:07.530 --> 1:14:08.813
but surviving them.

1:14:10.700 --> 1:14:12.653
- And you think you can?

1:14:12.653 --> 1:14:15.820
(soft dramatic music)

1:14:27.360 --> 1:14:28.590
- Yes?

1:14:28.590 --> 1:14:29.880
- Is Julian home?

1:14:29.880 --> 1:14:30.713
- No.

1:14:32.507 --> 1:14:33.993
- Hey, I'm Nick.

1:14:37.696 --> 1:14:40.697
I've been trying to reach
him for like a week.

1:14:40.697 --> 1:14:42.639
I haven't heard back from him.

1:14:42.639 --> 1:14:44.290
- Well, he's going through
something right now,

1:14:44.290 --> 1:14:46.023
so just give him some time.

1:14:48.505 --> 1:14:49.480
- I mean, is this normal?

1:14:49.480 --> 1:14:50.420
Does he just take off for days

1:14:50.420 --> 1:14:52.200
at a time without telling anybody?

1:14:52.200 --> 1:14:53.059
- Yeah, sometimes.

1:14:53.059 --> 1:14:54.690
And he always comes back
feeling a lot better,

1:14:54.690 --> 1:14:57.288
so just give him some space.

1:14:57.288 --> 1:14:58.705
- What's he upset about?

1:14:58.705 --> 1:14:59.930
- That's none of your business.

1:14:59.930 --> 1:15:00.900
- Hey.

1:15:00.900 --> 1:15:02.300
Sorry.

1:15:02.300 --> 1:15:04.452
I'm just really fucking worried about him.

1:15:09.870 --> 1:15:11.910
- He should be coming home soon.

1:15:11.910 --> 1:15:12.743
- How do you know?

1:15:12.743 --> 1:15:13.840
What makes you so sure?

1:15:13.840 --> 1:15:16.440
- Well, he wasn't planning
on leaving for long.

1:15:16.440 --> 1:15:18.627
His car's right outside.

1:15:18.627 --> 1:15:20.245
- Do you have a key?

1:15:20.245 --> 1:15:23.412
(soft dramatic music)

1:16:25.660 --> 1:16:26.493
Hey, man.

1:16:27.469 --> 1:16:29.571
Do you mind taking a look at this, please?

1:16:29.571 --> 1:16:32.737
(soft dramatic music)

1:16:34.753 --> 1:16:37.483
Dude, please look at this.

1:16:40.154 --> 1:16:41.952
- What is this?

1:16:41.952 --> 1:16:44.370
- I found it in Julian's car.

1:16:45.330 --> 1:16:46.780
- Is this a camera?

1:16:46.780 --> 1:16:50.219
- Yeah, he uses it when
he's like driving people.

1:16:50.219 --> 1:16:51.862
- Ew, a creepy recording.

1:16:51.862 --> 1:16:53.075
- Can you just play it?

1:16:53.075 --> 1:16:55.075
- Yeah okay, I'm trying.

1:17:00.942 --> 1:17:02.290
- What's taking so long?

1:17:02.290 --> 1:17:03.782
- It's loading, Nick.

1:17:06.910 --> 1:17:07.983
- Okay, that one.

1:17:07.983 --> 1:17:09.733
That one right there.

1:17:17.384 --> 1:17:20.384
(suspenseful music)

1:17:28.227 --> 1:17:29.443
- [Rianne] Holy shit.

1:17:30.539 --> 1:17:33.313
This could be enough to send him to jail.

1:17:34.318 --> 1:17:36.719
(suspenseful music)

1:17:36.719 --> 1:17:39.577
- [Nick] Why'd he wait until right now?

1:17:39.577 --> 1:17:41.559
- This is exactly what you needed.

1:17:41.559 --> 1:17:44.559
Okay, maybe he's gonna
confess to killing the others.

1:17:44.559 --> 1:17:46.952
- Why'd he wait until I got
out of prison to kill Julian?

1:17:46.952 --> 1:17:50.370
Why'd he wait so many years?

1:17:50.370 --> 1:17:51.202
I don't.

1:17:51.202 --> 1:17:52.090
- Hey, Nick, look.

1:17:52.090 --> 1:17:52.923
Listen to me.

1:17:52.923 --> 1:17:54.250
You have to go to the police.

1:17:59.973 --> 1:18:01.993
- Porter has to die.

1:18:01.993 --> 1:18:05.160
(soft dramatic music)

1:18:08.219 --> 1:18:09.291
- Nick.

1:18:09.291 --> 1:18:12.459
(soft dramatic music)

1:19:26.736 --> 1:19:27.568
You can do this.

1:19:27.568 --> 1:19:29.081
You can do this.

1:19:29.081 --> 1:19:32.248
(soft dramatic music)

1:19:34.580 --> 1:19:35.883
Hey, hey, can you help me?

1:19:37.559 --> 1:19:40.780
I got a flat tire and nobody came

1:19:40.780 --> 1:19:42.933
and I don't know how to take the tire off.

1:19:45.550 --> 1:19:47.930
- Well, if it's just a flat,
it shouldn't be a problem.

1:19:47.930 --> 1:19:49.480
I can change it for you.

1:19:49.480 --> 1:19:50.313
- Thank you.

1:19:50.313 --> 1:19:52.496
Thank you so much.

1:19:52.496 --> 1:19:53.580
- No problem.

1:20:00.559 --> 1:20:02.350
- [Rianne] I'm just getting nervous

1:20:02.350 --> 1:20:03.873
because there's nobody around.

1:20:06.210 --> 1:20:07.400
- Totally.

1:20:07.400 --> 1:20:09.499
I saw some homeless people
camping in the area.

1:20:09.499 --> 1:20:11.260
I mean, that doesn't mean anything but-

1:20:11.260 --> 1:20:13.800
- Yeah, that's what I was talking about.

1:20:13.800 --> 1:20:15.414
- You have a spare?

1:20:15.414 --> 1:20:16.623
- In the trunk.

1:20:19.550 --> 1:20:20.620
- [Katie] Do you live around here?

1:20:20.620 --> 1:20:21.452
- Not really.

1:20:22.960 --> 1:20:24.197
- We met before?

1:20:24.197 --> 1:20:26.760
You look so familiar.

1:20:26.760 --> 1:20:27.743
- I would remember.

1:20:29.405 --> 1:20:32.755
- Well, you are kind of
cute, so maybe that's why.

1:20:32.755 --> 1:20:35.755
(suspenseful music)

1:20:56.002 --> 1:20:58.701
(gun firing)

1:20:58.701 --> 1:21:01.868
(soft dramatic music)

1:21:36.065 --> 1:21:37.282
- Hey boo.

1:21:37.282 --> 1:21:40.450
(soft dramatic music)

1:21:45.910 --> 1:21:47.094
If this is about you moving in-

1:21:47.094 --> 1:21:48.662
- Sh.

1:21:48.662 --> 1:21:51.829
(soft dramatic music)

1:21:59.925 --> 1:22:01.710
- Is everything okay?

1:22:01.710 --> 1:22:05.460
(soft dramatic music)

1:22:05.460 --> 1:22:06.293
- Yeah.

1:22:07.478 --> 1:22:09.431
I just need a minute.

1:22:09.431 --> 1:22:12.598
(soft dramatic music)

1:22:20.330 --> 1:22:22.386
- You sure everything's okay?

1:22:22.386 --> 1:22:25.553
(soft dramatic music)

1:22:33.511 --> 1:22:36.178
(alarm beeping)

1:22:44.689 --> 1:22:47.856
(soft dramatic music)

1:23:11.688 --> 1:23:12.793
- Excuse me.

1:23:14.270 --> 1:23:15.323
- Ah, Rianne.

1:23:16.170 --> 1:23:17.300
Good morning.

1:23:17.300 --> 1:23:21.677
If you're looking for Professor
Rossi, he's not in today.

1:23:21.677 --> 1:23:23.197
- How come?

1:23:23.197 --> 1:23:24.450
- I don't know.

1:23:24.450 --> 1:23:26.400
He's always been here earlier than normal

1:23:26.400 --> 1:23:29.410
and today he just wasn't.

1:23:29.410 --> 1:23:31.600
- Did you try calling him?

1:23:31.600 --> 1:23:34.803
- Well, it's more complicated than that.

1:23:34.803 --> 1:23:36.530
- Look, I'm not gonna leave

1:23:36.530 --> 1:23:38.918
until you tell me what's going on.

1:23:38.918 --> 1:23:41.323
Sorry, I'm just being honest.

1:23:44.130 --> 1:23:48.370
- A couple of police
detectives were here earlier.

1:23:48.370 --> 1:23:52.330
Professor Rossi's neighbors
heard gunshots yesterday

1:23:52.330 --> 1:23:53.743
and they called the police.

1:23:54.610 --> 1:23:56.378
When the officers arrived,

1:23:56.378 --> 1:23:58.952
they walked in and found basically-

1:24:00.192 --> 1:24:02.780
- They broken in probably.

1:24:02.780 --> 1:24:05.590
- They walked in and they
found nothing strange

1:24:05.590 --> 1:24:09.869
other than a strong smell of bleach.

1:24:09.869 --> 1:24:11.919
- Like somebody had cleaned up the place.

1:24:12.947 --> 1:24:15.440
- Yes, Rianne, like a crime scene,

1:24:15.440 --> 1:24:17.809
but don't jump to conclusions.

1:24:17.809 --> 1:24:20.030
The officers, they arrived
there fairly quickly,

1:24:20.030 --> 1:24:23.760
so it's hard to imagine
that someone did something

1:24:23.760 --> 1:24:25.790
and then they had time to clean up.

1:24:25.790 --> 1:24:27.930
- What else did the detectives say?

1:24:27.930 --> 1:24:29.193
Any homicide detectives?

1:24:30.077 --> 1:24:32.830
- They were just asking routine questions.

1:24:32.830 --> 1:24:35.330
It's not a missing person case yet.

1:24:35.330 --> 1:24:36.910
- So we're just hoping
that Professor Rossi

1:24:36.910 --> 1:24:39.639
will show up at a later
day, today or tomorrow,

1:24:39.639 --> 1:24:41.663
and just tell us what happened.

1:24:41.663 --> 1:24:42.963
- Pretty much.

1:24:44.327 --> 1:24:47.040
Is there something I could help you with?

1:24:47.040 --> 1:24:48.980
- No, I just I had some questions

1:24:48.980 --> 1:24:51.670
about my senior project, but I can wait.

1:24:51.670 --> 1:24:52.940
I'll check back in tomorrow.

1:24:52.940 --> 1:24:53.773
Thanks.

1:24:53.773 --> 1:24:54.606
- Mm hm.

1:25:04.350 --> 1:25:06.960
- Mom, what are you doing here?

1:25:06.960 --> 1:25:09.580
- I told them I'd work from home today.

1:25:09.580 --> 1:25:12.232
Do you know where your brother is?

1:25:12.232 --> 1:25:13.065
- No.

1:25:13.930 --> 1:25:15.620
I was at Mariah's all day yesterday

1:25:15.620 --> 1:25:18.050
and then I went straight to school.

1:25:18.050 --> 1:25:21.032
- He didn't come home last night.

1:25:21.032 --> 1:25:23.407
- Maybe he's with Julian.

1:25:23.407 --> 1:25:24.702
- No, I don't think so.

1:25:26.130 --> 1:25:28.063
He sent me this text last night.

1:25:29.871 --> 1:25:32.910
I need some time away.

1:25:32.910 --> 1:25:34.410
Don't worry about me.

1:25:34.410 --> 1:25:35.243
Love you.

1:25:36.860 --> 1:25:38.059
Weird, right?

1:25:38.059 --> 1:25:39.577
- No.

1:25:39.577 --> 1:25:41.400
I mean, he has the money you gave him.

1:25:41.400 --> 1:25:43.180
He probably just needs some time off.

1:25:43.180 --> 1:25:46.160
- Yeah, but it just doesn't seem like him.

1:25:46.160 --> 1:25:48.877
- Mom, you just gotta give him some time.

1:25:49.764 --> 1:25:52.916
- I just thought that he
would stay a little longer.

1:25:52.916 --> 1:25:56.083
(soft dramatic music)

1:26:18.400 --> 1:26:20.690
- I'll be at Mariah's if you need me.

1:26:20.690 --> 1:26:22.163
- Are you coming back tonight?

1:26:27.360 --> 1:26:28.666
- I'll see you at dinner.

1:27:05.541 --> 1:27:06.540
- Let's get going.

1:27:06.540 --> 1:27:07.553
- Holy fuck.

1:27:18.068 --> 1:27:20.930
The cops are looking for you.

1:27:20.930 --> 1:27:24.150
- They probably don't even
know where to start yet.

1:27:24.150 --> 1:27:26.553
(soft dramatic music)

1:27:26.553 --> 1:27:28.829
- You set Nick up.

1:27:28.829 --> 1:27:30.130
- You're welcome.

1:27:30.130 --> 1:27:31.360
You wanted to get rid of him.

1:27:31.360 --> 1:27:32.573
I just played along.

1:27:36.110 --> 1:27:37.277
- Where is he?

1:27:38.258 --> 1:27:41.210
- Might wanna get rid of that video.

1:27:41.210 --> 1:27:43.532
It could link you to some bad mojo.

1:27:46.520 --> 1:27:48.100
- You were waiting for him.

1:27:48.100 --> 1:27:51.021
That's why the place was
clean when the cops arrived.

1:27:51.021 --> 1:27:53.433
- Glad to see your
education wasn't wasted.

1:27:57.018 --> 1:27:58.969
- What happens next?

1:27:58.969 --> 1:28:00.884
- We draw Katie out.

1:28:00.884 --> 1:28:01.717
- We?

1:28:02.647 --> 1:28:04.860
- Just a figure of speech.

1:28:04.860 --> 1:28:07.371
- How are you gonna draw Katie out?

1:28:07.371 --> 1:28:09.853
- Her mom lives in the same place.

1:28:12.430 --> 1:28:13.880
- What if Katie doesn't show?

1:28:14.827 --> 1:28:16.493
- Why wouldn't she?

1:28:20.224 --> 1:28:22.307
- There's plenty options.

1:28:24.630 --> 1:28:28.120
- You think Gwen loved
Katie more than anyone else?

1:28:28.120 --> 1:28:30.190
- I don't think it matters anymore.

1:28:32.523 --> 1:28:33.821
- Pull over.

1:28:33.821 --> 1:28:36.987
(soft dramatic music)

1:28:41.160 --> 1:28:41.993
- Wait.

1:28:43.389 --> 1:28:44.933
What are you really asking me?

1:28:46.050 --> 1:28:49.823
- Do you really think love
survives the object of affection?

1:28:50.790 --> 1:28:52.190
- It depends.

1:28:52.190 --> 1:28:56.141
Are you talking obsession
based love or deep caring love?

1:28:56.141 --> 1:28:57.891
- Is the answer different for each?

1:28:59.389 --> 1:29:00.223
- Yes.

1:29:01.126 --> 1:29:04.610
Obsession based love
may become more intense.

1:29:04.610 --> 1:29:08.830
Like any obsession intensifies
by the absence of the object

1:29:08.830 --> 1:29:12.090
because it'll be fueled
by fantasies and what ifs.

1:29:12.090 --> 1:29:14.950
On the other hand, deep caring
love may become more subdued

1:29:14.950 --> 1:29:18.013
because of the acceptance
of loss as facts.

1:29:19.487 --> 1:29:22.739
- You have a beautiful mind, Rianne.

1:29:22.739 --> 1:29:25.906
(soft dramatic music)

1:29:29.326 --> 1:29:31.076
- What just happened?

1:30:15.527 --> 1:30:18.193
(phone ringing)

1:30:22.096 --> 1:30:23.430
Hey, babe.

1:30:23.430 --> 1:30:24.900
- I love you tons, boo.

1:30:26.080 --> 1:30:28.093
- Babe, where are you?

1:30:28.093 --> 1:30:31.280
- Did you really think I
didn't know it was you?

1:30:31.280 --> 1:30:33.947
(ominous music)

1:30:35.760 --> 1:30:37.493
- What are you talking about?

1:30:37.493 --> 1:30:40.982
- You knew Katie wasn't coming
back because you killed her.

1:30:40.982 --> 1:30:43.333
That's all I wasn't sure about.

1:30:46.290 --> 1:30:48.083
- If this is your idea of a joke.

1:30:49.240 --> 1:30:51.490
- [Cameron] I'm a hopeless
romantic actually.

1:30:52.624 --> 1:30:54.593
Look on the table.

1:30:54.593 --> 1:30:57.260
(ominous music)

1:31:21.752 --> 1:31:23.469
- What do you want?

1:31:23.469 --> 1:31:26.736
- I want to know why you killed Gwen.

1:31:26.736 --> 1:31:29.403
(ominous music)

1:31:33.240 --> 1:31:35.226
Did you really love her?

1:31:35.226 --> 1:31:37.893
(ominous music)

1:31:43.416 --> 1:31:46.050
- I thought I was special to her.

1:31:46.050 --> 1:31:48.933
- Yet you replaced her so easily.

1:31:50.460 --> 1:31:52.193
- She has nothing to do with this.

1:31:53.240 --> 1:31:55.200
- [Cameron] Of course she does.

1:31:55.200 --> 1:31:57.683
I'm gonna show you what
love is really about.

1:31:59.325 --> 1:32:01.403
- I don't love that bitch.

1:32:02.240 --> 1:32:03.073
Let her go.

1:32:03.073 --> 1:32:04.860
- [Cameron] You know the thing about love

1:32:04.860 --> 1:32:09.090
is once it's in your
bones, it never goes away.

1:32:09.090 --> 1:32:10.580
- No, that's just a fixation.

1:32:10.580 --> 1:32:14.020
Love nurtures, heals, protects.

1:32:14.020 --> 1:32:15.297
- I did all that.

1:32:16.141 --> 1:32:17.910
I healed her wounds.

1:32:17.910 --> 1:32:19.550
Nurtured her passions.

1:32:19.550 --> 1:32:22.184
I protected her from her own insecurities.

1:32:22.184 --> 1:32:24.219
- That was a long time ago.

1:32:24.219 --> 1:32:26.430
- [Cameron] Maybe you can
follow your own advice

1:32:26.430 --> 1:32:31.059
and just move on, but if not,

1:32:31.059 --> 1:32:33.913
how can you escape the
prison of her absence?

1:32:34.850 --> 1:32:37.183
- Just let her go please.

1:32:38.320 --> 1:32:41.317
- [Cameron] How long do you
think you can go without her?

1:32:43.295 --> 1:32:45.712
- Look, I'll do anything you want.

1:32:45.712 --> 1:32:47.190
- Anything.

1:32:47.190 --> 1:32:49.090
- Just let her go.

1:32:49.090 --> 1:32:50.639
- I always liked you, Rianne,

1:32:50.639 --> 1:32:52.719
but not even you can imagine the pain

1:32:52.719 --> 1:32:54.053
of going on without her.

1:32:56.059 --> 1:32:57.032
- What do you want?

1:32:57.032 --> 1:32:58.132
Would you just say it?

1:33:00.250 --> 1:33:01.773
- [Cameron] I want you to be free.

1:33:04.000 --> 1:33:05.150
- Don't do this.

1:33:05.150 --> 1:33:08.358
- Go to the balcony and climb out.

1:33:08.358 --> 1:33:11.025
(ominous music)

1:33:28.880 --> 1:33:32.219
- Just put her on the phone please.

1:33:32.219 --> 1:33:33.202
- I'm sorry, boo.

1:33:33.202 --> 1:33:34.618
I don't know what happened.

1:33:34.618 --> 1:33:35.752
- It's okay.

1:33:35.752 --> 1:33:37.133
It's okay, babe.

1:33:37.133 --> 1:33:39.800
(ominous music)

1:33:41.223 --> 1:33:42.123
I love you tons.

1:33:44.690 --> 1:33:45.573
- [Cameron] I'm waiting.

1:33:47.323 --> 1:33:48.156
Now fly.

1:33:52.014 --> 1:33:54.764
(dramatic music)
